dashboard.definition:
{
    "title": "About OAI",
    "description": "Ollama Integration for Splunk",
    "inputs": {},
    "defaults": {
        "dataSources": {}
    },
    "visualizations": {
        "viz_features": {
            "options": {
                "markdown": "## Features\n\n- **Local Inference**: Works entirely against a local Ollama server (no external API key required)\n- **Model Selection**: Setup page auto-populates available models from `ollama list`\n- **Configurable**: Base URL, SSL verification, and timeout settings\n- **Simple Syntax**: `| oai \"your question\"`\n- **Debug Mode**: Optional `debug=true` to inspect payloads\n- **Persistence**: Optional `persist=true` to store responses in a Splunk index\n- **Investigation Mode**: Use `investigate=true` to analyze index data automatically"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_header": {
            "options": {
                "markdown": "# OAI (Observalitics AI) - Ollama Integration for Splunk\n\nA Splunk custom command for running prompts against a local Ollama instance."
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_support": {
            "options": {
                "markdown": "## Support\n\n- Ensure Ollama is running on the configured host/port (default: `http://localhost:11434`; switch to https if your deployment supports TLS)\n- Verify the desired model is pulled using `ollama list`\n- Check logs at `$SPLUNK_HOME/var/log/splunk/oai.log`\n\n## Requirements\n\n- **Splunk Enterprise 8.0+** (uses Python 3.7+; tested on Splunk 9.x/10.x with Python 3.9)\n- **Ollama** installed and running with at least one model pulled\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - See LICENSE file for details."
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        },
        "viz_usage": {
            "options": {
                "markdown": "## Usage Examples\n\n### Simple Chat\n```spl\n| oai \"What is machine learning?\"\n```\n\n### Specify Model\n```spl\n| oai model=\"qwen2.5:1.5b-instruct\" prompt=\"Give me three facts about Splunk.\"\n```\n\n### Debug Mode (preview what is sent to Ollama)\n```spl\n| oai debug=true prompt=\"Explain observability.\"\n```\n\n### Persist Output (uses configured index)\n```spl\n| oai persist=true \"Store this answer\"\n```\n\n### Persist to Custom Index (override config)\n```spl\n| oai persist=true persist_index=my_index \"Store in a specific index\"\n```\n\n### Investigate Index\n```spl\n| oai investigate=true \"index=_internal summarize events\"\n```\n\n### Investigate with Filters\n```spl\n| oai investigate=true \"index=_internal sourcetype=splunkd log_level=ERROR summarize the errors\"\n```\n\n### Classify Events (streaming mode)\n```spl\nindex=_internal | head 3 | oai \"What can you tell me about these events? Classify them.\"\n```"
            },
            "type": "splunk.markdown"
        }
    },
    "dataSources": {},
    "layout": {
        "globalInputs": [],
        "layoutDefinitions": {
            "layout_1": {
                "options": {
                    "display": "actual-size",
                    "height": 1200,
                    "width": 950
                },
                "structure": [
                    {
                        "item": "viz_header",
                        "position": {
                            "h": 70,
                            "w": 910,
                            "x": 20,
                            "y": 20
                        },
                        "type": "block"
                    },
                    {
                        "item": "viz_features",
                        "position": {
                            "h": 170,
